assessment_details.task_description:
Students are required to work in a team to complete background research on their selected topic and present their findings during tutorial discussion. The team* presentation will include:

Background research about a selected social problem, taking a national and/or international perspective on the issue;

Background research on key target markets impacted by the problem/issues

Analysis of the problem by presenting a situation analysis of stakeholder influences, marketing impacts and policy issues;

Problem statement (that demonstrates an understanding and analysis of the issue based on relevant and up to date information);

The scoping research phase in social change intervention design is critical to avoid generating and crafting solutions before a deep understanding of the customer is achieved, and ensures that the intervention design has a clear behaviour change focus (and not just an awareness campaign).

Presentation requirements : Students should plan for their team presentation to be 15 minutes in length. The presentation should include: background research, a situation analysis, problem statement, identified target market issues and ethical considerations. On the day of the presentation student will be required to upload a copy of their presentation slides to turnitin.

Research: Students are expected to use academic and industry/news references, and synthesise academic and industry secondary research to obtain a passing grade.

Summative Peer Assessment: All team member are required to complete a group peer assesssment after completion of the team presentation. This process enables the collection of student responses on the contribution of individual group members to the assessment activity and may impact marks.

Teams: Students should form teams of 3 students from their tutorial group
